profileText: a Representative from Illinois; born in Chicago, Cook County, Ill., April 13, 1964; graduated from Carl Sandburg High School, Orland Park, Ill.; attended Marquette University, Milwaukee, Wis.; B.A., University of Wisconsin Madison, Madison, Wis., 1986; advertising executive; consultant; non-profit executive; unsuccessful candidate for nomination to the One Hundred Sixteenth Congress in 2018; elected as a Democrat to the One Hundred Seventeenth Congress (January 3, 2021 – Present).
